sequenceDiagram
    participant Botnet as DDoS Botnet<br/>100K+ devices
    participant BGP as BGP / Anycast<br/>Route Distribution
    participant PoP1 as CDN PoP 1<br/>New York
    participant PoP2 as CDN PoP 2<br/>London
    participant PoP3 as CDN PoP 3<br/>Tokyo
    participant XDP1 as XDP/eBPF<br/>Kernel Filtering
    participant L7 as L7 Analysis<br/>WAF + Bot Detection
    participant Origin as Origin Server

    Note over Botnet,Origin: Volumetric DDoS Attack - 5 Tbps UDP Flood

    Botnet->>BGP: 5 Tbps attack traffic<br/>targeting 104.16.132.229

    Note over BGP: Anycast distributes attack<br/>across ALL PoPs automatically

    BGP->>PoP1: ~1.7 Tbps (US sources)
    BGP->>PoP2: ~2.0 Tbps (EU sources)
    BGP->>PoP3: ~1.3 Tbps (APAC sources)

    Note over PoP1,PoP3: Each PoP handles a fraction<br/>No single PoP overwhelmed

    PoP1->>XDP1: Packets enter kernel
    Note over XDP1: XDP processes at line rate<br/>BEFORE kernel network stack<br/>- IP reputation check<br/>- Rate limiting<br/>- Protocol validation<br/>- Pattern matching

    XDP1->>XDP1: Drop 99.5% attack packets<br/>(malformed UDP, known bad IPs,<br/>rate limit exceeded)

    XDP1->>L7: 0.5% passes to L7<br/>(potential legitimate traffic)

    L7->>L7: Analyze HTTP requests:<br/>- JS challenge for new IPs<br/>- JA3 fingerprint check<br/>- Behavioral analysis<br/>- Rate limiting per session

    L7->>Origin: Clean traffic only<br/>(~0.1% of original volume)

    Origin-->>L7: Normal response
    L7-->>PoP1: Response
    PoP1-->>BGP: Serve to legitimate users

    Note over Botnet,Origin: Attack absorbed. Origin never saw attack traffic.<br/>Legitimate users experienced no downtime.
